verbose_text: Intracoronary administration of an adenovirus vector encoding the human HGF gene (Ad-HGF) in patients with coronary heart disease, led to high expression of HGF and its receptor (c-met), augmented serum concentration of HGF, vEGF, MCP-1 and IL-10 and reduced serum concentration of IL-8, and increased the percentage of CD34 + and CD117 + cells in peripheral blood.
